'''Janet Holder''' was a Canadian business executive who headed [[Enbridge Northern Gateway Pipelines]].<ref>https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/careers/careers-leadership/enbridges-janet-holder-pushing-west-with-muscle/article4179871/?page=all</ref><ref>http://www.bnn.ca/News/2012/10/12/Enbridge-defends-Northern-Gateway-from-critics.aspx</ref><ref>http://www.theprovince.com/technology/Michael+Smyth+look+woman+behind+controversial+Northern+Gateway+Pipeline/8914078/story.html</ref><ref>http://www.enbridge.com/InvestorRelations/CorporateGovernance/ExecutiveManagement/Janet-Holder.aspx</ref>
With a chemical engineering degree from the [[University of New Brunswick]] and a master's degree in business from [[McMaster University]], Holder joined [[Enbridge]] in 1992.<ref>http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/janet-holder-public-face-of-the-northern-gateway-pipeline-project-dies-1.3211542</ref>
Holder was president of gas distribution at Enbridge from 2008 to 2011.<ref>http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/janet-holder-public-face-of-the-northern-gateway-pipeline-project-dies-1.3211542</ref> In 2011, Holder became the executive vice president of western access at Enbridge, which she held until 2014 when she retired from the position.<ref>http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/janet-holder-public-face-of-the-northern-gateway-pipeline-project-dies-1.3211542</ref>
